explanation: This solution uses a greedy approach to find the kth lexicographically smallest integer in the range [1, n]. It starts from 1 and iteratively moves to the right or down based on the number of steps available and the remaining k. The time complexity is O(log n) because the number of steps is roughly halved in each iteration.

